    "body": "The `RapidsHostMemoryStore` https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/blob/branch-23.02/sql-plugin/src/main/scala/com/nvidia/spark/rapids/RapidsHostMemoryStore.scala makes use of a pageable pool size, in addition to a pinned memory pool, and the regular host allocator.\r\n\r\nWe would like to understand if the pageable pool provides a meaningful speedup during our regular benchmarks under constraints GPU memory pools (such that we induce plenty of host spill). The theory is that having a pool of pageable memory allows the system to see these pages often, causing them to be registered and fast to transfer to/from, but we seem to lack the evidence to back that and are wondering if it would simplify the code to remove it.",
